endencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"In this program I added a hook working in info level, and it add a field:\r\n\r\n```\r\npackage main\r\n\r\nimport (\r\n\t\"github.com/Sirupsen/logrus\"\r\n)\r\n\r\ntype hook struct {\r\n}\r\n\r\nfunc (*hook) Levels() []logrus.Level {\r\n\treturn []logrus.Level{logrus.InfoLevel}\r\n}\r\n\r\nfunc (h *hook) Fire(entry *logrus.Entry) error {\r\n\tprintln(entry.Message)\r\n\tentry.Data[\"tag\"] = \"tag\"\r\n\treturn nil\r\n}\r\n\r\nfunc main() {\r\n\tlogrus.AddHook(&hook{})\r\n\tlogrus.Info(\"info\")\r\n\tlogrus.Error(\"error\")\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nAnd the output is:\r\n\r\n```\r\ninfo\r\ntime=\"2018-07-31T17:40:04+08:00\" level=info msg=info tag=tag\r\ntime=\"2018-07-31T17:40:04+08:00\" level=error msg=error tag=tag\r\n```\r\n\r\nBut there was still a `tag` field when I print error log. I found that the entry object reused from a pool in https://github.com/sirupsen/logrus/blob/master/logger.go#L79. But it didn't clear Data when it put back in pool or got from the pool. Is it a bug?","closed_by":{"login":"dgsb","id":5495748,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjU0OTU3NDg=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/5495748?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/dgsb","html_url":"https://github.com/dgsb","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dgsb/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dgsb/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dgsb/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dgsb/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dgsb/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dgsb/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dgsb/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dgsb/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dgsb/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"reactions":{